item.description: Our next meetup will be at Daniel Webster Wildlife Sanctuary in Marshfield, MA. This one will begin at 1:00 pm. (not the usual 11:00 am) This is an Audubon sanctuary and covers hundreds of acres of grassland, woodland and wetlands. For birders of all experience there are observation blinds overlooking wetland that attracts herons, egrets and shorebirds, as well as mink and muskrats. The weather is supposed to be very cooperative and give us a beautiful day. Let's all get out and enjoy a dry sunny day for a change. For those interested we will meet for lunch after the walk at a local restaurant.
